technology from aliens.

00:01:02.710 --> 00:01:06.450
&gt;&gt; On YouTube there seems to be some pretty
good evidence about it, but I don’t know.

00:01:06.450 --> 00:01:08.070
&gt;&gt; You have seen some videos of aliens.

00:01:08.070 --> 00:01:09.070
&gt;&gt; Yeah.

00:01:09.070 --> 00:01:10.070
&gt;&gt; That looked convincing.

00:01:10.070 --> 00:01:11.070
&gt;&gt; Kind of, yeah.

00:01:11.070 --> 00:01:18.060
&gt;&gt; So {?} apparently were beings that came
down from heaven according to the old Sumerian

00:01:18.060 --> 00:01:19.060
texts.

00:01:19.060 --> 00:01:22.920
&gt;&gt; The oil paintings and stuff and Sumeria.

00:01:22.920 --> 00:01:27.350
&gt;&gt; I think people believe that aliens have
visited us just because they are not aware

00:01:27.350 --> 00:01:29.909
of how vast the universe really is.

00:01:29.909 --> 00:01:32.560
I mean, what is an exoplanet?

00:01:32.560 --> 00:01:34.840
How far is a light year?

00:01:34.840 --> 00:01:38.609
These are the things you need to understand
if you are to judge the probability that alien

00:01:38.609 --> 00:01:40.759
life could come and visit us.

00:01:40.759 --> 00:01:44.829
What is a galaxy?

00:01:44.829 --> 00:01:46.149
&gt;&gt; Specifically I wouldn’t know.

00:01:46.149 --> 00:01:52.109
&gt;&gt; Is a galaxy something totally different,
like another universe maybe?

00:01:52.109 --> 00:01:55.240
&gt;&gt; A galaxy is a sun and a moon, isn’t it?&gt;&gt;

00:01:55.240 --> 00:02:02.860
So a galaxy is bigger than that.

00:02:02.860 --> 00:02:06.790
&gt;&gt; Galaxies, hundreds of stars, blah, blah,
blah.

00:02:06.790 --> 00:02:08.700
&gt;&gt; In fact, hundreds of billions of stars.

00:02:08.700 --> 00:02:09.770
&gt;&gt; Billions of stars.

00:02:09.770 --> 00:02:11.110
&gt;&gt; Yeah, hundreds of billions.

00:02:11.110 --> 00:02:12.110
&gt;&gt; Yeah, yeah.

00:02:12.110 --> 00:02:13.110
&gt;&gt; What is a galaxy?

00:02:13.110 --> 00:02:18.080
It is a collection of stars and gas that are
held together in a gravitationally bound system.

00:02:18.080 --> 00:02:20.990
Every point of light that you see here is
a star.

00:02:20.990 --> 00:02:24.400
When we say 200 billion stars, it is probably
at least 200 billion stars.

00:02:24.400 --> 00:02:27.340
The galaxy is 100,000 light years across.

00:02:27.340 --> 00:02:32.440
So, you know, it is just... the distances
are unimaginable.

00:02:32.440 --> 00:02:34.910
One light year, don’t forget, is 10 trillion
kilometers.

